Under the UNDAF outcome 1 "Economic growth is more equitable, inclusive and sustainable" and UNDP Strategic areas of support "Pro-poor development planning, poverty monitoring and MDG reporting", the project will directly contribute to the (2006-2010) UNDP Country Programme Document's output of "Improved design and more effective implementation of national target programme for poverty reduction (NTPPR) and national programme for socio-economic development for poorest mountainous and ethnic minority communes (P135)".
Increased the effectiveness of the two programmes will be achieved through (i) more transparent and participatory programme design process that also creates opportunities for innovations and knowledge sharing1, (ii) strengthening of management and operational systems such as M&E, targeting and budget allocation and financial management, and (iii) building programme staff's and people's capacity for decentralized and accountable local-level planning and implementation. Specifically, the project will focus on achieving the following outputs:
Output 1:	The targeted programmes for poverty reduction and its implementation guidelines are designed in a transparent and participatory manner, are gender-sensitive and take into account the lessons learnt;
Output 2:	Efficient and participatory M&E systems at central and local levels established to systematically monitor progress of the targeted programmes on poverty reduction and disseminate outputs timely to the wider public and policy makers for continuously increasing program effectiveness;
Output 3:	Effective mechanisms for improved targeting and participation are in place that enhance the poor's access to and benefits from the targeted programmes; 
Output 4:	Transparent and participatory budget allocation and financial managements systems established and used for targeted poverty reduction programs;
Output 5:	Improved capacity of responsible programme staffs, including the people themselves, for more effective and participatory decentralized local level planning, implementation and monitoring of the targeted programmes at all levels.

